at ONA, the Online News Association Conference, tomorrow,

00:07:33.920 --> 00:07:34.640
yes?

00:07:34.680 --> 00:07:35.320
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:07:35.320 --> 00:07:37.170
And I think we're going to release this thing if we

00:07:37.170 --> 00:07:38.280
get the final, go ahead.

00:07:38.540 --> 00:07:41.480
Where we went in Chicago, working on behalf of the philanthrop

00:07:41.480 --> 00:07:44.410
ist, the philanthropic group press forward to say, let

00:07:44.410 --> 00:07:45.500
's map your ecosystem.

00:07:45.500 --> 00:07:48.660
The amount of, like, ethnic groups, of, like

00:07:48.660 --> 00:07:53.400
, immigration communities who have these creators on TikTok, who then

00:07:53.400 --> 00:07:56.080
have private WhatsApp groups, was a thing we found there.

00:07:56.100 --> 00:07:57.100
We're still doing research.

00:07:57.100 --> 00:07:58.600
I don't know if we're going to have it all

00:07:58.720 --> 00:08:00.140
wrapped up in time for Monday or not.

00:08:00.240 --> 00:08:02.920
But all the ways in which there's different models that are

00:08:02.930 --> 00:08:05.630
based on different platforms that, like what Lawrence said, of

00:08:05.630 --> 00:08:06.820
, like, we know we're going to be here to

