reach people.

00:08:07.380 --> 00:08:09.780
We know we can be here to monetize people.

00:08:09.780 --> 00:08:11.730
We know we can be here to do a version of R

00:08:11.730 --> 00:08:13.740
&D, of trying to, you know, rough out

00:08:13.740 --> 00:08:16.100
where else we'll kind of reach people at.

00:08:16.120 --> 00:08:19.540
It's an incredible series of portfolios of what news creators

00:08:19.540 --> 00:08:22.110
are doing to build, to reach, and to monetize

00:08:22.110 --> 00:08:22.420
.

00:08:24.060 --> 00:08:27.530
I think that that's such an interesting segue to a sort

00:08:27.530 --> 00:08:32.230
of broader topic about when you talk often about software platforms and

00:08:32.320 --> 00:08:34.430
protocols and things like that, there's a lot of,

00:08:34.430 --> 00:08:36.430
like, discussion about, oh, well, we just need

00:08:36.530 --> 00:08:39.850
people to exclusively use our platform to switch from some other platform

00:08:39.850 --> 00:08:40.740
to our platform.

00:08:40.780 --> 00:08:43.370
And once you go up a strata from that and you

00:08:43.370 --> 00:08:48.410
're thinking about people who are community organizers or community leaders,

00:08:48.900 --> 00:08:51.860
their strategies around how they're connecting with audiences, the afford

00:08:51.860 --> 00:08:54.740
ances different tools give them, I think is a really important

00:08:54.740 --> 00:08:56.120
thing for people to think about.

00:08:56.120 --> 00:08:59.450
And I'm really curious about how, say, local news

00:08:59.450 --> 00:09:02.760
international is thinking about their presence and where you feel you need

00:09:02.880 --> 00:09:04.800
to be and where you would like to be.

00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:06.560
Yeah.

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:09.250
The notion of exclusivity, I think, makes a lot

00:09:09.350 --> 00:09:12.420
of sense for most industries, but maybe not for the news

00:09:12.420 --> 00:09:13.380
, for a couple of reasons.

00:09:13.380 --> 00:09:16.900
First of all, philosophically, we believe we want everyone

00:09:16.940 --> 00:09:18.350
to see our content.

00:09:18.520 --> 00:09:21.650
So we want to put it in the broadest possible places

00:09:21.650 --> 00:09:24.840
we can because we want to be sort of democratic in that

00:09:24.960 --> 00:09:25.440
way.

00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:28.720
We know, though, that we can monetize people in

00:09:28.720 --> 00:09:31.120
different ways because of that.

00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:33.380
We sort of want to reach the broadest audience, but

00:09:33.410 --> 00:09:35.560
ultimately we want to build fans over time.

00:09:35.560 --> 00:09:37.240
That's kind of been the goal Dave and I had in

00:09:37.240 --> 00:09:39.770
mind since we launched in 2019 is, like, do the

00:09:39.770 --> 00:09:42.530
news, build fans, and then you can do something with

00:09:42.730 --> 00:09:43.200
those fans.

00:09:44.420 --> 00:09:47.640
So you can monetize those fans, but ultimately we want

00:09:47.640 --> 00:09:50.740
to deliver the news in any way, in any place where

00:09:50.860 --> 00:09:52.050
the audience is.

00:09:52.140 --> 00:09:54.550
It doesn't mean we need to be everywhere, but we

00:09:54.550 --> 00:09:57.370
need to be sort of in the broadest possible audience grab

00:09:57.370 --> 00:09:57.630
.

00:09:58.820 --> 00:10:01.510
It's classic top of funnel, I guess, traditionally speaking

00:10:01.610 --> 00:10:01.780
.

00:10:01.780 --> 00:10:04.470
Yeah, I think the only thing I'll, I mean

00:10:04.570 --> 00:10:08.300
, again, I could listen to Lauren talk about this forever

00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:08.720
.

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:11.610
It is endlessly fascinating with me to think about people who every

00:10:11.610 --> 00:10:13.630
day wake up and say, I'm going to think about

00:10:13.640 --> 00:10:14.240
the news.

00:10:14.240 --> 00:10:15.640
What stories are in our pocket?

00:10:15.640 --> 00:10:16.760
What have we been looking for?

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:18.800
What are the longer term stories?

00:10:19.740 --> 00:10:22.420
I think especially this community, especially, again, just reflecting

00:10:22.420 --> 00:10:24.420
on Aaron's amazing, you know, speech this morning,

