how do we kind of, like, graph onto something here

00:10:45.970 --> 00:10:47.410
to torture a word, I guess.

00:10:48.920 --> 00:10:51.080
News flows all day, every day.

00:10:51.080 --> 00:10:52.970
It just, you know, Lauren wakes up every day and

00:10:53.030 --> 00:10:53.960
has a million ideas.

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:55.260
She's so good with Dave.

00:10:55.260 --> 00:10:56.290
You guys figure out, we'll do this, we'll

00:10:56.290 --> 00:10:57.000
do this, we'll do this.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:10:58.350
And if we want to get to this, that's actually

00:10:58.350 --> 00:10:59.020
a four-day thing.

00:10:59.020 --> 00:11:00.040
We'll kind of get there.

00:11:00.040 --> 00:11:02.180
That's in the guts of a news person.

00:11:02.180 --> 00:11:04.150
As I think about the builders, as I think about the

00:11:04.150 --> 00:11:07.040
community organizers, I think about people who are thinking about paid

